		<title>The basics of an impeccable order taking service</title>
		<link>https://www.fusionbposervices.com/blog/order-taking-service.html</link>
				<comments>https://www.fusionbposervices.com/blog/order-taking-service.html#respond</comments>
				<pubDate>Thu, 02 Feb 2012 09:16:05 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Alicia Johnson]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[order taking service]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[customer call center]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.fusionbposervices.com/blog/?p=4462</guid>
				<description><![CDATA[Increasing number of business enterprises are resorting to a customer call center in order to reap the benefits of their quality order taking answering service. Such service has become important in conducting business affairs due to the recent changes the business firms have adopted particularly when it comes to marketing their products. Extensive use of [&#8230;]]]></description>
								<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Increasing number of business enterprises are resorting to a customer call center in order to reap the benefits of their quality order taking answering service. Such service has become important in conducting business affairs due to the recent changes the business firms have adopted particularly when it comes to marketing their products. Extensive use of telemarketing and web marketing tools has made high tech <strong><a title="order taking service" href="http://www.fusionbposervices.com/order-taking.html">order taking service</a></strong> mandatory.</p>
<p>How do the call center companies do their job? Let’s have a look.</p>
<p><strong>Taking down customer orders</strong>: When taking down orders is the main concern, it is of utmost importance that the agents listen to the customers carefully. During the training it is been repeatedly advised to them to repeat the orders in order to avoid any mistakes.</p>
<p><strong>Maintaining records</strong>: The customer care representatives are also responsible for maintaining the records and details of the orders. This not only helps in the entire process of order management but is also crucial for future references in case there are any problems with the orders.</p>
<p><strong>Inventory management</strong>:  Proper management of the Inventory is also a part of the responsibility of the call center agents. Keeping a track of the stocks is important for the perfect execution of the order taking duties.</p>
<p><strong>Dispatch and delivery of the orders</strong>: The responsibility of the customer care representatives does not really end with taking down orders. They need to process the orders to the concerned business departments. Early dispatch and delivery of the orders to the customer’s doorsteps is also their responsibility.</p>
<p>In short the customer call centers are responsible for speeding up the entire sales cycle. And it is the efficiency of the agents that has a decisive impact on the reputation of the business. Hence the entire process is being monitored and supervised thoroughly.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
